Well this is the new version of this map. There are a few secret rooms if you can find them. There is also 3 working elevators and a back stairway in case the security lockout is engaged. Also for the elevators, up is "s" and down is "w".

Also, by request, you can get on the roof of the courtyard and the secret room with the monitors isn't as cheap anymore. 2 ways to get into that area. Also the elevator shafts are fixed along with the vents. There are now boxes to get up if security is enabled.

Another update is the lighting. The street lights are updated, more realistic with the lighting. Also there is now 2 more rooms along the stairs and there is also there is another secret room. The security room is now updated so you don't get stuck in the teleporter and it is bigger now. Also there is now a train station and it has a few extra rooms down there.

The outside area is updated and has one of those combine outpost things. Also there is an added trap over there. More rooms/ updates to come in the final.

BTW nav file uses old version. No problems known with it, but in the final it will be updated. Also B3 was skipped since testing was local.

Enjoy!

My latest and best project so far! Enjoy! If you upload this map on your server please post the IP! [GameplaY] - 64 spawn points - Many well balanced hiding places (climbing, barricading and traps) - 1 secret hiding place (shoot the wall above the door of the house, where the urn is) - Very high framerate, no lags [Design] - High level of detail - 3d skybox - Cubemaps Unfortunately I had to turn HDR off because it reduced FPS too much in some areas (although I optimized as much as possible). [Update History] - (08.03.2010) v2:        now for 64 players! - (10.03.2010) v3:        added some hiding places (barricading) and a connection between helipad and villa! - (11.03.2010) v3_fix:  fixed a leak... - (15.03.2010) v4:        balanced camping spots, fixed a bug with the traps (they can't be blocked by weapons anymore) - (15.03.2010) v5:        made storage room spots weaker and the traps dont kill instantly anymore (20 dmg only and players are teleported away)

zm\_clouds by Soft Serve (a.k.a. Satin Storm)

Features:

- A map that scales well for both high and low population servers.
- Special item: speedsuit.
- Several secrets.

ZM_CLOCKS_FINAL
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This map was inspired by zm_lila_panic in the way that I frowned upon it.

Recommended Players: Up to 32
Maximum Players/Spawnpoint Count: 64

ZM_CLOCKS is a map that takes place in a small, dusty, and abandoned town. Players spawn in a wide open area, then must scatter to find a place to camp before the starting zombie(s) get them. There's many places a player can go once they spawn. There's a large, four-floored building, a hidden easter egg area, the tops of neighborhood buildings, the classic "cart and two tanks", two small alleyways, atop a garbage container, atop the white truck, and much more.

This map was based on zm_lila_panic, but the map itself was made from scratch and is not a reskin or remake. I incorporated the good parts of zm_lila_panic, like the teamwork and gameplay, and left out the sheer ugliness of the map and its use of fullbright. This map is dust-based and uses a few prefabs from the actual map de_dust, so you know it's not ugly. The FPS count is actually about 20 frames higher than zm_lila_panic, yet this map looks better and is x2 the fun.

This took over 10 hours to make, which is pretty long for its size, since the map itself is just as big as the base of zm_lila_panic, yet it looks larger because of its detail. I hope you guys enjoy it. All of the bugs and graphical errors have been wrung out in advance, so people can just enjoy themselves.

As for the clock, well, it actually works. Look closely and you'll see the hands moving quite accurately, just faster than usual. Time goes by quickly when you're having fun. =P

<u>FIXED VERSION UPDATE:</u>
- Totally optimized; higher FPS count.
- 2 New Areas/Buildings.
- Added wall to building set for more interesting gameplay.
- Remade ladder placement for balance.
- Reworked camping areas for balance and gameplay.
- Darkened the map for a more realistic feel.
- Fixed annoying texture from accidental model textures.
- Minor bug fixes.
- Minor graphical fixes.

Regards,
Grey-Echo (£cho)
FPSBanana ZombieMod Representative

My first map. May be a bit laggy on old computers.

This map can be played as zombie or regular, however regular gameplay may seem somewhat repetative. The main feature is the highrise office with all floors accessable. It was a drawn out project so the map may be inconsistent. I'm very happy with the way lighting appears in the warehouse, but most other lighting was annoying and again, last minute.

There was a lot of gameplay design on the office building, as well as a lot of invisible walls to stop exploiting. One secret area. Smoke effects may slow low end PCs. Nav included.

This map has not yet been used on a zombie server yet (soon to come to a server). If you want to use it, feel free! :D

ZM_CITY_GRAVEYARD v 1.0 ------------------------------ The town of Timtamville has been overrun by brain-eating Zombies!! The streets are full of chaos, as citizen after citizen falls prey. Take the advice of Father Grigori who stands on the clifftop - get out while you still can!! And if you can't do that, "AIM FOR THE HEAD!!" zm_city_graveyard is the first Zombie Mod map by A.o.F. the SEAL / Predulus Version 1.0 of zm_city_graveyard supports up to 40 players. SPECIAL FEATURES --------------------- - Custom Nav file with place names (so your radio messages are useful!!) - NPC zombies (on fire) running about chasing some poor suckers - Father Grigori, the Mad Monk from HalfLife2!! - Some music from Michael Jackson's Thriller soundtrack - Spooky Thriller voice-over from by legerdary horror actor Vincent Price - 3D skybox - Several secrets - Lots of stuff to blow up - Lots of blood, fire and brain-eating fun!! *Some buildings borrowed from HL2 - thanks to Valve :D

Overview: This map is set around an alley way, set in the still standing City 19. The problem is that the only few surviving humans are stuck here do to the combine's quarantine of the city. The only thing left to do is SURVIVE!. Gameplay: Got my inspiration for this map from different areas in HL2. In this map i really tried to focus on game play and looks. . Many of the ZM maps out there are heavy on gameplay but look like crap. Lots of props to throw around, has a very dark feel to it. FLASHLIGHT is YOUR FRIEND! There are 24 spawns scattered all around the map in different areas. You can explore most buildings, V2 hope to make it so you can go in ALL buildings. THis is only version 1 Im going to begin work on version 2 and hopefully fix a few bugs.
